#30500
Vestibule of the Celestial Tower~
The frigid temperatures outside suddenly give way to warmth in this foyer.  
It is a relatively small room with a door to the east and the west.  Each door
glows softly with an unnatural hue.  The eastern side of the room is crafted
from what appears to be a single peice of something like quartz crystal, while
the western side of the room is made from seamless polished black basalt that
is cool to the touch despite the ambient warmth.  There is a large steel
plaque embeded in the northern wall.  
~
305 0 0 0 0 0
D1
A single solid sheet of quartz crystal barricades the path.  There are no obvious keyholes, and the door appears to glow with a bluish tint.
~
door~
2 30502 30501
D3
A huge single sheet of basalt halts your progress west.  The stone is cool to
the touch and glows with a faint blue aura.  
~
door~
2 30503 30515
E
plaque~
   The Celstial Tower - Prison of the Southern Fringe

                *  The Improsoned  *

Ser Alrec Greystone of Tyvar, son of Ser Edwin Greystone.
Ser Demetrius Greystone of Tyvar, son of Ser Edwin Greystone.

Only the gravest of crimes warrant banishment to the fringe realms.
Herein the judged remain exiled, never again to feel the warmth of
the empire.
~
S
#30501
Perimeter Hall~
You are in a narrow hallway running along the interior perimeter of the spire.
The walls and ceiling appear to be made from a solid, opaque quartz crystal.
The cloudy white walls are polished and smooth.  Every several feet there is a
glowing orb within the crystal of the ceiling above, bathing the hallway in a
calm yellow light.  A red carpet with golden trim runs up the hallway to the
north, and the western exit leads to the vestibule.  
~
