#30513
Eastern Foundation Core~
This domed room is quite different from the angular halls of the east.  The
perfectly domed ceiling goes all the way to the floor, giving the room a round
shape.  At the top in the center of the dome, there is a brightly shining
globe embedded in the crystal above.  The walls in this room are smooth, but
have a very coarse texture to them and are unpolished.  Within the crystal
wall to the right, there are nine beams of light about three feet tall, and
each of them glow a bright green.  Above each beam of light there is a small
panel.  There is also a small flat workspace carved into the southern wall.  
There is a large silver door to the north, and a smaller silver door to the
east.  
~
305 0 0 0 0 0
D0
A large silver door blocks the way to the north.  It is cold to the touch, and
is polished to an almost mirror-like shine.  There is a small triangular
recepticle in the door.  
~
door~
2 30504 30514
D1
A smooth, almost mirror finished, metal door blocks the eastern exit.  There
is a simple metal handle on the otherwise smooth door.  There are no obvious
locks or hinges on the door.  
~
door~
